{"id": "EUVD-2025-20978", "enisaUuid": "a3bdbad6-bae7-3fe9-9bdc-fa5fde9555d6", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet: drv: netdevsim: don't napi_complete() from netpoll\n\nnetdevsim supports netpoll. Make sure we don't call napi_complete()\nfrom it, since it may not be scheduled. Breno reports hitting a\nwarning in napi_complete_done():\n\nWARNING: CPU: 14 PID: 104 at net/core/dev.c:6592 napi_complete_done+0x2cc/0x560\n  __napi_poll+0x2d8/0x3a0\n  handle_softirqs+0x1fe/0x710\n\nThis is presumably after netpoll stole the SCHED bit prematurely.", "datePublished": "2025-07-10T09:32:28", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-20T18:31:00", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a8ff2e362d901200a1075c3ca9c56d9c7bbef389", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6837dd877270c57689bd866de9f3de14172c2439", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1264971017b4d7141352a7fe29021bdfce5d885d", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38270"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38270"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "518fb95c-741a-3564-965b-e352ce488fe1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3762ec05a9fbda16aaaa2568df679ab8ad13f38d <6837dd877270c57689bd866de9f3de14172c2439"}, {"id": "583b910d-4c63-3ce4-be60-984c8c6a41d8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3762ec05a9fbda16aaaa2568df679ab8ad13f38d <a8ff2e362d901200a1075c3ca9c56d9c7bbef389"}, {"id": "72e19d8e-7ec7-3a33-9ebf-5dbdd6a1a3d4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16-rc2"}, {"id": "755f8da9-9feb-3e27-83d6-621911485011", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15.3"}, {"id": "870ff2c9-58b7-3888-a81c-f21abea2d286", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "3762ec05a9fbda16aaaa2568df679ab8ad13f38d <1264971017b4d7141352a7fe29021bdfce5d885d"}, {"id": "b043d405-3fad-38d9-abd4-305ef354806a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.10"}, {"id": "b392bf31-caf0-3849-bd39-0e0a